title: Locally compiled and on-chain bytecode do not match!
body:
### Environment information

* `brownie` Version: Brownie v1.18.2
* `ganache-cli` Version: v6.12.2
* `solc` Version: 0.8.14
* Python Version: 3.10.4
* OS: linux

### What was wrong?

MBP-de-Luis-2:nft luissiqueiros$ brownie run scripts/simple_collectible/deploy_simple.py --network rinkeby
Brownie v1.18.2 - Python development framework for Ethereum

NftProject is the active project.

`Running 'scripts/simple_collectible/deploy_simple.py::main'...
rinkeby
Transaction sent: 0x48c101a922b677d083d5e7de80107cbb9ef8fa83b5264fc99fd55999c8926fb4
  Gas price: 1.000000017 gwei   Gas limit: 2017295   Nonce: 56
  SimpleCollectible.constructor confirmed   Block: 10751953   Gas used: 1833905 (90.91%)
  SimpleCollectible deployed at: 0x6e7b0C5011c391723F0BF4c6e186e17F688f19d1

/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.10/lib/python3.10/site-packages/brownie/network/contract.py:1198: BrownieCompilerWarning: 0x6e7b0C5011c391723F0BF4c6e186e17F688f19d1: Locally compiled and on-chain bytecode do not match!
  warnings.warn(`

### How can it be fixed?

Fill this in if you know how the bug could be fixed.
